stylometry: The logical upper limit is something that is used to tell the solver and the reader of the spreadsheet what the maximum number of something that you can produce.  For example we may be deciding on three books to produce and how many of each.  Well we can only produce so many of each in a certain time period, this is our logical upper limit.  For this logical upper limit you will have to put as a constraint in solver, for example, b2(logical upper limit) <= h12:k12 (number of book 1 to produce).  This is important because it is impossible for us as a company to produce more than our logical upper limit.
